{
  "text": "Restrictive lung disease was defined according to ATS/European Respiratory Society (ERS) criteria, defined as a TLC<80% [CITATION_1] 22] . In order to examine whether respiratory muscle weakness may be associated with the outcomes, we performed a sensitivity analysis using two additional definitions of restrictive lung disease. The first definition required both TLC<80% and a FEV1/FVC ratio >0.7. The second alternative definition required the same, and also required a low probability chest image, one that provided no evidence for a parenchymal explanation for a restrictive pattern.",
